laboratory_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated up to 15 mm in diameter with a fluid-filled lumen and hyperenhancement with surrounding fat stranding and a few small probably reactive nodes in the right lower quadrant measuring up to 5 mm in shortest dimension. There is no evidence for abscess or perforation.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: A persistent ill-defined soft tissue density correlating with an opacity visible on a remote prior CT that has not really changed since that time. The nodule in the right lung base and left lower lobe are unchanged from prior examinations.

laboratory_examinations.findings: MIXED BACTERIAL FLORA (>= 3 COLONY TYPES), CONSISTENT WITH SKIN AND/OR GENITAL CONTAMINATION.
